The paper deals with the problem of how social media users can estimate their followers' preferences and decide which stories to share next to receive more positive feedback. This problem is related to social media, user behavior, and decision making, which are all covered by the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). The paper also uses statistical hypothesis testing and utility maximization, which are covered by the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
